Let me analyze this task step by step:

1. Analyzing the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of 8 blocks in total
- It has 4 layers/levels
- Colors used: Red, Green, Yellow/Orange, and Orange
- The blocks are arranged vertically with specific geometric configurations

2. Selecting Blocks from Dictionary:
Based on the target image, I'll need the following blocks:
- Block 9 (Orange vertical column)
- Block 6 (Green vertical column)
- Block 7 (Yellow horizontal block)
- Block 2 (Red arch block)
- Block 10 (Yellow half-moon block)
- Block 14 (Orange triangular block)

3. Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (Orange vertical column)
    Step2: Move block with index 7 (Yellow horizontal block) on top of the orange column
    Step3: Move block with index 6 (Green vertical column) on top of the yellow block
    Step4: Move block with index 10 (Yellow half-moon block) on top of the green column
    Step5: Move block with index 2 (Red arch block) on the right side
    Step6: Move block with index 14 (Orange triangular block) on top to complete the structure
}
